The paper deals with deep learning and compression techniques for resource-constrained embedded devices, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on deep learning and neural networks suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the most likely category. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for sensing applications points towards cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as other possible categories. The use of compression techniques and the focus on resource-constrained devices suggest cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as additional categories.
